ğŸ§© What is a CMS (Content Management System)?

A **CMS** allows users to **create, edit, manage, and publish website content** without writing code every time.

ğŸ”¹ Why CMS is Important

* Easy content updates
* Non-technical users can manage websites
* Faster development and maintenance


ğŸ†š CMS Comparison: WordPress vs Payload CMS

ğŸŒ WordPress (Traditional CMS)

* Most popular CMS in the world
* Powers **43%+ websites**
* Started in 2003 as a blogging platform
* Built using **PHP**

âŒ Limitations of WordPress

* Slower for modern applications
* Harder to scale
* Less flexible with modern frontend frameworks
* Limited control for developers

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš¡ Payload CMS (Modern CMS)

* Built with **JavaScript / TypeScript**
* Runs on **Node.js**
* Designed for modern web apps

âœ… Advantages of **Payload CMS**

* Full frontend control
* Works smoothly with **Next.js**
* Faster performance
* Scalable for large applications
* Better **data ownership & privacy**
* Tracks content changes (`createdBy`, `updatedBy`)

ğŸ“Œ **Why companies are shifting:**
Modern CMS = speed + flexibility + control

