ğŸ”„ What is DNS (Domain Name System)?

DNS converts **human-friendly domain names** into **IP addresses** so browsers can locate servers.

ğŸ“Œ Example:
`google.com` â†’ `142.250.xxx.xxx`


ğŸ” DNS Resolution Process

1. Browser sends request
2. DNS Resolver checks cache
3. Queries:

   * Root server
   * TLD server (.com, .in)
   * Authoritative server
4. IP address returned
5. Website loads

â±ï¸ Happens in milliseconds

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“¦ DNS Caching & TTL

* **DNS Cache** stores previous lookups
* **TTL (Time To Live)** defines cache duration
* Lower TTL = faster updates but more queries


ğŸ§¾ Common DNS Record Types

| Record | Purpose                       |
| ------ | ----------------------------- |
| A      | Maps domain â†’ IPv4            |
| AAAA   | Maps domain â†’ IPv6            |
| MX     | Email routing                 |
| CNAME  | Domain alias                  |
| TXT    | Verification & email security |
| NS     | Name servers                  |
| SRV    | Service location              |
| PTR    | Reverse DNS lookup            |

